SUMMARY:Tech as Cognitive Accessibility: Designing Systems for ADHD Brains
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['Accessibility'\, 'ITS']\\nCategory: Lecture/Pan
 el Discussion\\nTech as Cognitive Accessibility: Designing Systems for ADH
 D Brains with A11yTalksPresenter:Eleanor Beilby (She/Her)Description:ADHD 
 involves executive dysfunction\, time blindness\, and working memory barri
 ers that standard technology often overlooks. Cognitive accessibility\, un
 like sensory or motor access\, is still largely treated as a productivity 
 problem rather than an access problem. This session reframes digital tools
  as cognitive accessibility aids\, presenting inclusive design patterns\, 
 no-code workflows\, and real examples of technology that support ADHD cogn
 ition instead of overwhelming it.\\nDetails: https://swatcentral.swarthmor
 e.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1412435743
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1412435743
CATEGORIES:Lecture/Panel Discussion
END:VEVENT
