SUMMARY:Exhibit: The Hidden World of Fungi
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['Swarthmore College Libraries'\, 'Cooper Series'
 \, 'William J. Cooper Foundation']\\nCategory: Exhibit\\nFungi have long b
 een entangled with the history of Swarthmore. Displayed here are items fro
 m the Friends Historical Library\, Rare Book Room\, Peace Collection\, Col
 lege archives\, and Biology Department archives\, spanning over 500 years 
 of human entanglement with the fungal kingdom. Welcome to the understory. 
 View the AccessAble USA guide for McCabe Library. View the AccessAble USA 
 guide for Swarthmore College. For directions\, parking\, and a campus map\
 , please refer to Visit Swarthmore. This exhibit is a part of Swarthmore F
 ungi Fest\, which is free and open to the public. Some individual events m
 ay require registration in advance.  Swarthmore Fungi Fest is supported b
 y the Cooper Foundation\, Swarthmore College Libraries\, the Biology Depar
 tment\, the Campus and Community Store\, the English Department\, the Envi
 ronmental Studies Program\, the Film and Media Studies Department\, Kitao 
 Gallery\, the Office of Sustainability\, Scott Arboretum & Gardens\, with 
 a special thanks to our local mycology clubs\, the Philadelphia Mycology C
 lub and the New Jersey Mycological Association.\\nDetails: https://swatcen
 tral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1406737159
LOCATION:McCabe Library Ad Hoc Exhibit 1
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1406737159
